         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>74</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1993"/><citedRange>191</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">You (have gone?) into the <hi>nirvāṇa</hi> – may you listen attentively to this! For these are Tuṣita gods who were your relatives.</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">You (have gone?) into the nirvāṇa—may you listen attentively to this! For these are Tuṣita gods who were your relatives.  (cf 74)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>368</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3 #a4 #a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>64</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3 #a4 #a5 #b1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1954c"/><citedRange>110</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>129, 160</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Dir, dem Schutz [und] der Hoffnung der Welt, taten sie [scil. die Wesen] bitteres Leid: Hände [und] Füße schnitten sie dir ab; wo [bzw. wann] auch immer stachen sie dir die Augen aus; die diademgeschmückten Häupter schnitten dir die Rücksichtslosen ab; sie quälten dich [und] kochten dich; die Knochen spalteten sie dir klein; die Haut zogen sie dir vom Körper ab und schnitten dir alles Fleisch ab: Du [aber] warst nie ärgerlich [wtl. gestört, verstört] auf sie, auch ließ dein Denken nie nach. Nach den Leben des Gesetzes als dem besten, nach dem eben begehrtest du [immer wieder] mit Verlangen.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">On you, the shelter [and] hope of the world, they [i.e. the beings] inflicted bitter suffering: hands [and] feet they cut from you; where [when?] ever they stung out your eyes; your heads adorned with diadems the ruthless ones cut off; they tortured you [and] cooked you; your bones they cracked to small bits;  [your] skin they drew from your body and all the flesh [they] cut from you: [but] you were never vexed with them, also your thinking never declined. [It was] for the life of the law as the best [possible life], for this exactly you [always] longed with desire.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>103, 129, 137, 160</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4 #a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:krause1952"/><citedRange>205</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:krause1952"/><citedRange>27</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1989"/><citedRange>35</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>88, 140</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>137</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>118</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5 #b1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>103</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>65</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1958a"/><citedRange>151</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>383</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1989"/><citedRange>35</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:meunier2013"/><citedRange>150</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">tu as pris part à toutes les choses accumulées avec tant de souffrance.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2 #b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>506f</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Du tröstestest sie [scil. die Wesen] [und] riefst sie [und] machtest andere [welt]überdrüssig [mit den Worten]: "O, [ihr] Lieben, genießt doch nur diesen Gesetzestrank!"</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">You comforted them [i.e. the beings] [and] called them [and] made others [world-]weary [saying]: "Oh, [you] dear ones, do savour this potion of the law!"</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>383, 506-7</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein2012"/><citedRange>125</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">The manner of others, however, is this: if they find the jewel that they search with eagerness,</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3 #b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Wenn sie das Juwel, nach dem sie da sehnsüchtig [wtl. mit Verlangen] suchen, finden, verstecken sie es insgeheim.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">When they find the jewel that they are seeking with longing, they will hide it secretly.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>151, 402</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3 #b4 #b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">The manner of others, however, is this: if they find the jewel that they search with eagerness, they hide it secretly. More than all, over all, and from all, this manner of yours distinguishes itself. That is why deep [lit. broad] love to you, o help and stay, has come to me.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>673</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>128</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>261</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">they hide it secretly. More than all, over all, and from all, this manner of yours distinguishes itself. That is why deep [lit. broad] love to you, o help and stay, has come to me.</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Mehr als alles, über alles hinaus, von allem unterscheidet sich diese deine Art.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">More than everything, above everything, from everything this your manner differs.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>113</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>47 n.3</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Das [ist] deine Allerkenner-Kraft und dies unser Vermögen: [Im Vergleich] mit dem Feind der anityatā [Unbeständigkeit], [nämlich] mit dir, werden wir unterliegen. ODER: Das [ist] deine Allerkenner-Kraft und dies unser Vermögen, [das im Vergleich] mit dem Feind der anityatā, [nämlich] mit dir, unterlegen [ist].</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">This [is] your omniscient power and this our ability: [in comparison] with the enemy of the anityatā [inconstancy], [that is], with you, we will succumb. OR: This [is] your omniscient power and this our ability, [which, in comparison] with the enemy of the anityatā, [that is], with you, [is] inferior.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>47-8</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
